------=_NextPart_000_0302_01C88DF2.582EC000
Content-Type: text/plain;
	charset=&quot;us-ascii&quot;
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit

Yes Judy - Goldwave is audio software that is used on the computer.  It
takes all audio files and works with them speed up or slowing down, maxing
or minimizing volume, listen to your audio forward or backwards, etc.  You
can put it on your laptop and then upload to the yahoo group so we can all
hear.  There is free audio software called Audacity, there is also other
popular software out there that know people use like cool edit pro, etc.

k



  _____  

From: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com [mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com] On Behalf Of
judy_in_hollywood
Sent: Monday, March 24, 2008 8:33 PM
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Subject: [EVP-ITC] Re: RS-12-469 How to slow down scan/voices????



--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups &lt;mailto:EVP-ITC%40yahoogroups.com&gt; .com, Rhonda W
&lt;rhondak1973@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt; If you use a recording program ...like Goldwave...you can actually 
slow them down while you listen to the playback, can ever listen to 
them backwards. But I dont know of a way to slow down the sweep. 
Are you using the AM or FM band? And have you tried switching to the 
other band(the one ur not using)? Ive tried a session on the FM band 
but it doesnt really seem to work for some reason but the AM does 
good and Ive gotten a response that indicates that they agree with 
the AM being better here.
&gt; 
&gt; Rhonda Hi Rhonda, I&#39;m not sure what Goldwave is (is it 
used on a computer?)! I am currently online at the local library&#39;s PC 
as at home I only have a Webtv unit to go online & that&#39;s limited! I 
have a Laptop, but it&#39;s not connected to the internet - as I use it 
with DVD&#39;s or software programes only. =Judy= 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; judy_in_hollywood &lt;Ticket_to_Heaven@...&gt; wrote:
&gt; Hi All, Have been doing sessions and sometimes get a 
voice or more that 
&gt; just jumps in and says a word or two durring the scan, but most of 
the 
&gt; time it seems it&#39;s like a room full of people talking very fast and 
&gt; thus I can&#39;t seem to hear them well enough to hear if they are 
giving 
&gt; me any messages! Am I the only one with this issue? How can I slow 
this 
&gt; down to hear better? =Judy= P.S. I only use the RS 12-469 with 
&gt; portable folding Craig speakers & a Sony cassette recorder with 
&gt; earphones (cups over ears). I sometimes use an external mic or just 
the 
&gt; cassette recorder&#39;s mic.
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; ---------------------------------
&gt; Never miss a thing. Make Yahoo your homepage.
&gt;




